<H3> <TI>   Beijing Celebrates Sino-Tunisian Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1001092394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0809 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1001092394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 10 (XINHUA) -- A diplomatic 
function was held here today to celebrate the 30th anniversary 
of the establishment of diplomatic relations between China and 
the Republic of Tunisia. 
  Chinese Assistant Foreign Minister Wang Changyi and Tunisian 
Ambassador to China Mohamed Habib Kaabachi attended the function 
given by the Chinese People's Association for Friendship With 
Foreign Countries (CPAFFC). 
  In his speech, CPAFFC President Han Xu noted that in the 
past 
30 years the two countries have supported each other politically 
and cooperated with each other economically and have made big 
progress in their relations of friendship and cooperation in all 
domains on the basis of the five principles of peaceful 
co-existence. 
  He said that his institute is ready to do its part to 
promote 
further development of Sino-Tunisian ties. 
  Tunisian Ambassador Kaabachi said "though far away from each 
other, Tunisia and China are linked together by friendship." 
  The Tunisian Government pays great attention to its ties 
with 
China and hopes that these ties would be further developed, he 
added. 

