<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Report on Jiangxi Industrial Production </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1101102894 Nanchang Jiangxi People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1100 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1101102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nanchang Jiangxi People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] In 1993, the industrial production in this 
province, on the basis of the previous year's fast and efficient 
growth, maintained a strong momentum of development. The 
industrial output value generated throughout the year was 87.89 
billion yuan, up 38.2 percent over the previous year. The net 
increase of output value was 24.4 billion yuan. The combined 
industrial and agricultural output value was 121.6 billion yuan, 
up 27.1 percent. 
  Last year witnessed deepened reform, expanded opening up, 
and 
accelerated development in this province. The broad ranks of 
cadres and workers in the industrial and communication sector 
provincewide further implemented the spirit of the important 
talks of Comrade Deng Xiaoping, the 14th National CPC Congress, 
and the Third Plenary Session of the 14th CPC Central Committee. 
They emancipated their minds, forged ahead despite 
difficulties, and scored a victory in the third campaign of the 
effort to tackle key problems in industrial adjustment with 
conscientious efforts. They devoted much energy to enterprise 
reform, structural adjustment, strengthening of management, and 
acceleration of technical transformation, and succeeded in 
maintaining synchronized fast growth of industrial production 
speed and efficiency. 
  The characteristics of industrial production last year are 
as 
follows: First, strenuous efforts were made to implement the 
"Regulations on Converting the Operational Mechanisms of 
State-Owned Industrial Enterprises" and the implementation 
measures made by the provincial authorities. The number of 
joint-stock industrial and commercial companies rose to 26 and 
that of enterprises undergoing reform experiments conducted in 
light of the policies for Chinese- foreign joint ventures 
expanded to 230. There are now 36 standard enterprise groups 
and 110 small state-owned industrial enterprises run by local 
people all over the province. By the end of the third quarter 
of this year [as heard], there were over 33,000 township and 
town enterprises under the cooperative shares system. 
  Second, the internal management of enterprises, energy 
conservation, and cutting down of consumption were strengthened. 
In the industrial and communication sector, an extensive 
production and economy drive was carried out. The rate of 
energy conservation and consumption reduction province-wide was 
about 10 percent. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

