<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Industry Shows `Healthy Development' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0701151194 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1340 GMT 
7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0701151194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, January 7 (CNS)--Shanghai's industrial 
sector showed continuous, fast and healthy development in 1993 
with an industrial sales value of some RMB [Renminbi] 323.74 
billion, 21.1 percent up over the previous year, according to 
the Shanghai Bureau of Statistics. The ratio of production to 
sales reached 98 percent, the highest in China. 
  The development of foreign-funded enterprises in the city 
last year continued to retain its leading position among the 
various kinds of economies there with their sales value for the 
whole year put at RMB 54.35 billion [renminbi], up 65.4 percent 
over the previous year. Industry in the Pudong New Zone still 
kept the lead in the municipality with its growth of the ratio 
of production to sales there being 4.1 percentage points higher 
than the average for the municipality as a whole. 
  With last year's development the automobile industry, iron 
and steel, commmunications and power station equipment became 
the pillar industries in Shanghai. Outputs of 
technology-intensive products such as programme-control 
switchboards, synthetic rubber, big-sized integrated circuits, 
air-conditioners and video recorders all increased greatly. 
This indicates remarkable achievements in the adjustment of the 
internal structuring of Shanghai industry. 
  According to statistics, the economic results for industry 
in 
Shanghai had been further enhanced with the rate of profits tax 
to their assets, the rate of profits to their costs and their 
productivity all better than in the previous year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

