<H4>   Greeted by Thai Commander </H4>
<F P=102> OW0801004994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0311 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0801004994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Wang Weijun 3769 5898 6511] </F>
  [Text] Bangkok, 6 Jan (XINHUA) -- General Woranat 
Apichari, supreme commander of the Thai Armed Forces, held a 
banquet for Liu Huaqing, vice chairman of the Central Military 
Commission of the People's Republic of China, and his party this 
evening at Bangkok's Oriental Hotel. 
  General Woranat spoke at the banquet. He congratulated Liu 
Huaqing for receiving an Order of the Knight, First Class, from 
the King of Thailand. He expressed the hope to further 
strengthen friendship and cooperation between the peoples and 
armed forces of Thailand and China in the future. 
  In his speech, Liu Huaqing said that as an Asian nation, 
China sincerely hopes that the region will become one of 
stability, peace, and common development. He added that China 
is willing to make positive and unremitting efforts to achieve 
that goal together with other nations in the region. 
  Liu Huaqing and his party arrived here today and began their 
six-day official goodwill visit to Thailand. 

</TEXT>

