<H3> <TI>   Liu Huaqing on Official Visit to Thailand </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets Thai Generals </H4>
<F P=102> OW0801033794 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1057 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0801033794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Wang Weijun (3769 5898 6511)] </F>
  [Text] Bangkok, 7 Jan (XINHUA) -- This morning, General 
Woranat Aphichari, supreme commander of the Thai Armed Forces, 
and Major General Sombat Rotphonthong, Thai Deputy Defense 
Minister, respectively, met with and had cordial talks with Liu 
Huaqing, vice chairman of China's Central Military Commission, 
and his party, who are here on an official goodwill visit. 
  During the meeting, Woranat said Liu Huaqing's goodwill 
visit 
will surely contribute to strengthening the friendly 
relationship between the peoples and armies of the two 
countries. He added that the armed forces of the two countries 
will further develop traditional friendship, increase exchanges, 
and learn from each other in the future; this, he said, will be 
most beneficial to both parties. 
  Liu Huaqing said the people and the armed forces of China 
and 
Thailand maintain a good relationship and that there is no 
problem between them. He expressed the belief that such a 
relationship will surely be further enhanced and developed. 
  During the meeting, Sombat said Liu Huaqing's visit has 
great 
significance in strengthening the friendly relationship between 
the people and armed forces of the two countries. 
  Liu Huaqing briefed Sombat on China's achievements in 
economic construction and army building. He reiterated that 
China follows a good neighborly policy, will never seek 
hegemony, opposes power politics, and stands for settlement of 
disputes with friendly neighboring countries through peaceful 
means and dialogue. He added that both China and Thailand, to 
develop the economy and raise people's living standard, long for 
a peaceful and stable environment. 

</TEXT>

