<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liu Huaqing on Official Visit to Thailand </TI></H3>
<H4>   Visits Military Bases </H4>
<F P=102> OW1001145394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1424 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1001145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lop Buri, Thailand, January 10 (XINHUA) -- Liu 
Huaqing, vice chairman of the Chinese Central Military 
Commission, visited three Thai military bases today. 
  In the morning, Liu and his entourage arrived at U-tapao Air 
Base and Sattahip Naval Base, about 200 kilometers to the 
southeast of Bangkok. 
  Liu, on board an amphibious armored car, watched air and 
coastal defense soldiers' demonstrations of parashooting, motor 
boat chasing and cliff climbing. 
  In the afternoon, the group flew to the Royal Thai Army's 
Special Warfare Center in Lop Buri, about 160 kilometers to the 
north of Bangkok, and watched demonstrations of parashooting, 
ambush on the sea and commandos' rapid shooting. 
  During the visit, Commanding General of the Special Warfare 
Command Unit Lt Gen Surayut Chulanont awarded Liu Huaqing with 
an honorary medal of parashooters, which is normally conferred 
to senior Thai military officers and foreign military and 
political leaders. 
  On Saturday and Sunday, Liu visited Phuket, where he was 
welcomed by governor of Phuket, Sukit Nimikul. 

</TEXT>

