<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ren Jianxin Meets Indonesian Chief Justice </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0701143194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1408 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0701143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jakarta, January 7 (XINHUA) -- Ren Jianxin, 
visiting president of the Chinese Supreme People's Court, held 
talks here today with Purwoto S. Gandasubrata, chief justice of 
Indonesia. 
  During the talks, the two sides exchanged views on 
cooperation in the judiciary field. For his part, President Ren 
Jianxin raised five proposals which received positive response 
from the Indonesian side. 
  Ren Jianxin suggested to strengthen exchanges of visits 
between top judiciary leaders of the two countries. He invited 
Indonesian Chief Justice Purwoto to visit China at his 
convenience, and Purwoto accepted the invitation. 
  Ren Jianxin also proposed that the exchanges of visits will 
be held among local courts and ordinary justices between the two 
countries, adding that the two countries should provide each 
other with judiciary data and documents. 
  He wished that the two countries will continue to implement 
the memorandum of understanding on legal affairs cooperation 
signed by justice ministers of China and Indonesia in 1992. 
  He suggested that the two countries consider the signing of 
an agreement on judiciary assistance. 
  Chief Justice Purwoto briefed the Chinese guests on 
Indonesia's legal system and the working state of affairs of the 
court. 
  Earlier, President Ren Jianxin paid a courtesy call on H. 
Wahono [name as received], chairman of the House of 
Representatives and chairman of the People's Consultative 
Congress. 
  President Ren Jianxin and his entourage left here today for 
Yogyakarta and Bali. They will leave Indonesia on January 11 
for Singapore. 

</TEXT>

