<H3> <TI>   PRC Spokesman on Fighting in Afghanistan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0801105494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1046 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0801105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 8 (XINHUA) -- The Chinese 
Government today expressed concern over the situation in 
Afghanistan, urging the conflicting parties there to achieve a 
permanent ceasefire as soon as possible. 
  A Foreign Ministry spokesman voiced the concern when asked 
to 
comment on the current situation in afghanistan. 
  "Since the beginning of the new year, the civil war in 
Afghanistan has flared up again," the spokesman noted. 
  "The Chinese Government is deeply concerned with the 
development of the situation in Afghanistan and hopes that the 
conflicting parties there will set store by the interests of 
their country and people and work to realize a permanent 
ceasefire as soon as possible, so as to avoid bloodshed and 
settle their disputes through peaceful negotiations, hence 
achieving at an early date a restoration of domestic peace, 
national reconciliation and the rebuilding of the country," the 
spokesman said. 

</TEXT>

