<H3> <TI>   Guangdong Offers Ideas on Economic Work </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1001143294 Beijing RENMIN RIBAO in Chinese 30 Dec 93 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> HK1001143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing RENMIN RIBAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Liang Zhaoming (2733 0340 2494): "Guangdong's </F>
New Ideas on Economic Work for 1994"] 
  [Text] Guangzhou, 29 Dec (RENMIN RIBAO)--Guangdong has 
registered a sustained, high-speed, and healthy [chi xu kuai su 
jian kang 2170 4958 1816 6643 0256 1660] economic growth this 
year as a whole. Summing up the work in the past year, the 
provincial economic work conference, which was held a few days 
ago, also made arrangements for economic work next year and put 
new ideas forward. 
  It has been laid down that, in its economic work for next 
year, Guangdong will make strenuous efforts in three main 
fields, i.e. deepening reform, laying a good foundation, and 
raising efficiency. 
  Governor Zhu Senlin stressed: Next year we should emphasize 
breaking new ground in reform of the enterprise system and 
breakthroughs on important points to boost the overall 
situation. We should select five large and medium-sized state 
enterprises for experiments in establishing a modern enterprise 
system and coordinate state experiments in 100 enterprises. In 
terms of reform measures, we must, first, carry out the 
"Enterprise Law" and the "Regulations" and seriously make good 
the various powers and benefits of enterprises; second, reform 
the property rights system and accelerate establishment and 
amplification of the state assets management structure; and 
third, continuously expand the scope of experiments in a 
standardized enterprise joint-stock system and practice in a 
planned way a corporate system in state-owned enterprises. 

</TEXT>

