<H3> <TI>   Guangxi Frontier Troops Clear Mine Fields </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0601100494 Nanning Guangxi People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1130 GMT 26 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> HK0601100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nanning Guangxi People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In the six months ending on 24 December, more than 
26,000 Guangxi frontier troops had taken part in mine clearing 
missions covering a total area of 3.1427 million square meters, 
exceeding the target by 208 percent and providing a fine 
environment for trade exchanges and border people. 
  Since the beginning of the mine clearing mission, frontier 
troops from the Guangxi Military District have fulfilled in a 
timely manner mine clearing tasks in 12 trade ports, including 
Dongxing, Dongzhong, Aidian, and Youyiguan; 17 border trade 
sites, including Zhushan, Canzhan, Lihuo, Banlang, Beishanyouan, 
and Longyao; as well as along main routes. They have cleared 
mines from 118 sites and have marked those sites. 

</TEXT>

