<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Macao </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bank of China Macao Branch Profits Increase in 93 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0801143994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1413 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0801143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Macao, January 8 (XINHUA) -- Bank of China Macao 
branch reported an increase of over 10 percent in terms of its 
realized profits in 1993, as compared with the figure for 1992. 
  Bank savings rose by five percent over that of 1992 which 
was 
23.52 billion Macao patacas (about 3.5 billion U.S. dollars). 
An increase of 30 percent was also reported in terms of bank 
loans in 1993, much higher than the 11.2 billion Macao patacas 
(about 1.4 billion U.S. dollars) in the previous year. 
  According to an official with the bank, last year's bank 
loans were mainly used in industrial production and foreign 
trade, adding that the sharp increase in this regard had 
resulted from the huge demand of capital in Macao in the past 
year. 
  Bank of China Macao branch is one of the leading commercial 
banks in Macao. Currently, it has 20 sub-branches all over 
Macao. 
  In 1992, its realized profit stood at 34.5 billion Macao 
patacas (about 4.5 billion U.S. dollars) 

</TEXT>

