<H3> <TI>   Deng Xiaoping Inscribes School Paper's Title </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1101095594 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0900 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1101095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 5 Jan (XINHUA) -- The CHINA JUNIOR HIGH 
SCHOOL STUDENTS PAPER [Zhongguo Chuzhongsheng Bao 0022 0948 0443 
0022 3932 1032] today published a message which extends its 
heartfelt gratitude to all concerned teachers and friends. 
  The message said: In the past five years since its founding, 
the CHINA JUNIOR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS PAPER, as a young 
seedling, has enjoyed support and cultivation from various 
sectors. So many people who cherish the youth have extended 
their love: Proletarian revolutionaries of the older 
generation, including Comrade Deng Xiaoping, who inscribed our 
paper's title; Comrade Kang Keqing, who personally came to the 
press office to encourage us to produce a good paper for the 
children; and Bing Xin and Xia Yan, who are more than 90 years 
old and who inscribed for the paper.... We should diligentily 
carry out this sacred mission and wholeheartedly serve in this 
undertaking for young people. 

