<H3> <TI>   Chen Xitong, Others Attend Disabled Games Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1101140994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1355 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1101140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 11 (XINHUA) -- The Sixth Far East 
and South Pacific Games for the Disabled will be held in Beijing 
from September 4 to October 10 this year. 
  At Tuesday's [11 January] preparatory meeting of the 
organizing committee of the Far East and South Pacific [FESP] 
Games for the Disabled, it was disclosed that more than 2,000 
athletes have applied to compete in the upcoming games. 
  Deng Pufang, chairman of the Chinese Federation for the 
Disabled, presided over Wednesday's meeting during which Mayor 
of Beijing Li Qiyan and former Mayor of Beijing Chen Xitong both 
made speeches. 
  Chen Xitong said that the FESP games for the disabled are 
one 
of the major events of 1994 and are a hit event for the disabled 
people of the municipality. 
  Chen said that it is another opportunity to show the world 
China's openness to the outside world. He stressed, "Beijing 
will try its very best to guarantee the games a great success." 
  Li Qiyan said: "The Beijing municipal government will 
endorse 
the games in the aspects of organization, equipment and finance. 
It is another opportunity to present Beijing to the entire 
world." 
  Vice-Mayor of Beijing Zhang Baifa also attended the meeting. 

</TEXT>

