<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ren Jianxin Addresses National Meetings </TI></H3>
<H4>   Attends Higher Court Meeting 30 Dec </H4>
<F P=102> OW1101130994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0759 
GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> OW1101130994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By RENMIN RIBAO reporter Mao Lei (3029 4320) and XINHUA </F>
reporter Zhang Sutang (1728 1372 1016)] 
  [Text] Beijing, 30 Dec (XINHUA) -- A five-day national 
conference of presidents of higher courts ended in Beijing 
today. The conferees held: Strict administration of justice by 
the people's courts has a direct bearing on the normal operation 
of a socialist market economic system and the stability of 
market economic order; as well as the dignity and integrity of 
the socialist legal system and the image of the party and the 
government. Therefore, it is a sacred duty of the people's 
courts to strictly administer justice. Courts at various levels 
must regard strict enforcement of law and improved quality of 
justice as a task of primary importance, and make relentless 
efforts to carry out this task. 
  Ren Jianxin, member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central 
Committee and president of the Supreme People's Court, spoke at 
the conference. He said: To ensure strict administration of 
justice, courts at all levels must emancipate minds, seek truth 
from facts, make active exploration, be bold in practice, and 
further strengthen reform and construction of courts 
ideologically, organizationally, institutionally, and in their 
style of work so as to constantly perfect the socialist judicial 
system with Chinese characteristics. 
  He demanded that courts persist in exercising their judicial 
functions independently and under the party's leadership, do 
things strictly according to the law, and resolutely correct 
failure to abide by the law, lax law enforcement, and letting 
law-breakers go free, so as to safeguard the unification of the 
socialist legal system. Meanwhile, it is necessary to train a 
contingent of court personnel who have a strong political 
orientation, professional competence, and solid style of work, 
and who are honest in performing official duties, and strict in 
administering justice. 
  According to briefings, interference from local and 
departmental protectionism have affected the strict enforcement 
of law in the trial of a few cases by the people's courts in 
some localities, thus preventing the courts from bringing into 
full play their judicial functions, and undermining the dignity 
and integrity of the legal system. 
  The conferees called for upholding the principle of open 
trial to effectively guarantee the right of litigants to file 
law suits. It is necessary to conduct open investigation, 
cross-examination, debate, and trial to place the entire 
judicial process under the supervision of the people. 
  The conferees held: The strengthening of judicial 
supervision and enforcement of judicial discipline is an 
important means to guarantee strict administration of justice. 
Courts at all levels must further study and trial-implement a 
system of investigating wronged cases. Personnel liable for 
wrongdoings in handling cases must be affixed with 
administrative and legal responsibilities. Courts at the upper 
level must strengthen supervision over the judicial work of 
courts at the lower level, and must resolutely correct errors 
and unfair verdicts in law enforcement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

