<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Beijing TV Series on Deng Theory, Part 13 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1001004994 </F>
<F P=103> OW1001004994 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Beijing Central Television Program One 
Network in Mandarin at 0805 GMT on 5 January broadcasts the 13th 
and last in a series of 13 lectures on "Deng Xiaoping's Theory 
of Building Socialism With Chinese Characteristics." An 
editorial reporet describing the content of the 12th lecture in 
the series was published in the Political &amp; Social section of 
the 7 January China DAILY REPORT, page 12. 
  The 13th lecture, which lasts for 25 minutes, is entitled: 
"Further Strengthen Party Building According to the Requirements 
of the 14th CPC National Congress," and is given by Dai Zhou, 
director of the Propaganda Bureau under the Propaganda 
Department of the CPC Central Committee. 
  The last lecture begins by underlining the important role of 
the CPC in leading the Chinese people to establish a socialist 
market economy and achieve the second-step strategic goal of 
quadrupling the gross national product by the end of this 
century. Therefore, Dai maintains, it is imperative to build 
the party into a strong core of leadership in the great 
undertaking of building socialism with Chinese characteristics. 
  Discussing measures for strengthening party building, Dai 
stresses: Efforts must be made to persistently take Deng 
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics as the basic guideline in strengthening the 
building of the party in accordance with its basic line. 
Moreover, it is necessary to strictly handle party affairs to 
consolidate a high degree of the party's unity organizationally 
and in action. 
  Explaining the significance of party building under the new 
situation of reform and opening up, Dai points out that efforts 
should be made to improve the party's style of work, promote 
clean government, and fight corruption throughout the entire 
process of reform and opening the country to the outside world. 
At 0830 GMT the lecture concludes by calling for continuously 
strengthening and improving party building in the light of new 
circumstances and problems as well as newly-acquired experience. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

