<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujian Reportedly Increases GNP Ahead of Schedule </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1101123494 Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1101123494 </F>
<F P=104>  Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to statistics provided by the provincial 
statistical bureau, in 1993 Fujian's GNP was estimated at 95.349 
billion yuan, an increase of 25.4 percent over the previous year 
as calculated on comparable prices, being the second top 
production year since the founding of the PRC and also the top 
production year since the introduction of reform and opening up, 
thus quadrupling the 1980 strategic objective seven months ahead 
of schedule. 
  Yesterday the provincial government held a news briefing to 
report on the above situation. In the meantime, the news 
briefing pointed out: There are still outstanding problems in 
the province's current economic life. Its agricultural 
foundation is still weak, market price increases are 
comparatively high, the investment structure is not quite 
rational, funds are still short of supply, and agricultural 
production is proceeding with difficulties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

