<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Heilongjiang Mine Blast Kills 70 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0801053094 Hong Kong AFP in English 0503 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> HK0801053094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, Jan 8 (AFP)--A gas explosion ripped 
through a mine in the northeastern Chinese province of 
Heilongjiang in October, killing 70 miners, THE WORKERS' DAILY 
[GONGREN RIBAO] revealed Saturday. 
  The blast was sparked by a short circuit in the wiring 
system, igniting gas that had been allowed to build up in the 
shaft by the failure of the mine's ventilation system, the 
newspaper said. 
  All 70 miners working in the shaft at the time of the 
explosion were killed, it added. 
  The explosion at the Baohe mine followed a similar blast 
there in January 1991 that killed 53 workers. 
  Industrial accidents claimed 11,600 lives in China last 
year, 
more than double the 1992 figure. 

</TEXT>

