<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Continues Tour of Harbin </TI></H3>
<H4>   Attends Seminar on `Building Harbin' </H4>
<F P=102> SK0901050494 Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2200 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0901050494 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The three-day seminar on the strategy for building 
Harbin into an important international economic and trade city 
of Northeast Asia ended on the afternoon of 8 January. 
Attending the seminar were Li Ruihuan, standing committee 
member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and 
chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's 
Political Consultative Conference; Li Peiyao, vice chairman of 
the National People's Congress; and Sun Weiben, Shao Qihui, and 
Zhou Wenhua, leaders of Heilongjiang Province. 
  The specialists and scholars attending this seminar 
maintained: Harbin is in an advantageous geological position, 
has an age-old tradition of economic, trade, and cultural flows 
with foreign countries, solid scientific and technological 
strength, extensive international contacts, convenient 
communications and transportation facilities, and a flourishing 
and brisk market. In particular, the economic foundation based 
on relatively strong comprehensive functions and the favorable 
domestic and international economic environment make it 
completely possible for Harbin to become an important 
international economic and trade city. 
  At the closing ceremony held on the afternoon of 8 January, 
Suo Changyou, mayor of Harbin city, expressed in his speech: We 
should translate the achievements of this seminar to the 
development plans of Harbin city as quickly as possible, should 
strive to enhance Harbin people's understanding of the 
significance in building the important international economic 
and trade city of Northeast Asia, and should make concerted 
efforts to march toward the goal of building an important 
international economic and trade city of Northeast Asia. 

</TEXT>

