<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Wen Jiabao Inspects Jiangsu Province 13-18 Dec </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0801030394 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1021 
GMT 18 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> OW0801030394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Yin Xuecheng (3009 1331 2052)] </F>
  [Text] Nanjing, 18 Dec (XINHUA) -- During his inspection 
of Jiangsu's Huaiyin Prefecture, Wen Jiabao, alternate member of 
the Political Bureau and member of the Secretariat of the CPC 
Central Committee, stressed: Deepening rural reform and 
developing the rural economy is the basic requirement for the 
economy to develop rapidly and in a sustained and healthy manner 
[chi xu kuai su jian kang fa zhan he zheng ge gai ge kai fang 
shun li jin xing 2170 4958 1816 6643 0256 1660 4099 1455 0735 
2419 0020 2395 7245 7030 2397 7311 0448 6651 5887], and for the 
entire reform and opening up to advance smoothly. In the course 
of building a socialist market economic system, we should regard 
as an important task supporting major grain and cotton 
production areas in developing their economies and ensuring a 
steady increase in grain and cotton production; we should ensure 
that this task is properly carried out. 
  From 13 to 18 December, Wen Jiabao inspected the 
agricultural 
production and rural work and visited peasant households in 
Suqian, Shuyang, Hongze, Jinhu, and other cities and counties of 
Huaiyin City, and held discussions with local cadres on issues 
concerning the current rural reform and development. 
  Over the last few years, while ensuring a steady increase in 
grain production, Huaiyin City, located in the heartland of 
northern Jiangsu, has made use of local resources to forcefully 
develop a diversified economy and the processing of agricultural 
and sideline products, opening up a path for rural economic 
development that is in line with local reality and bringing 
about big changes in local rural areas. Wen Jiabao fully 
approved Huaiyin Prefecture's experience in agricultural and 
rural economic development and offered his opinions on deepening 
rural reform. He said: Rural reform is an important part of our 
efforts to build a socialist market economic system. From the 
very beginning, China's rural reform has been market-oriented. 
It has two important characteristics: First, peasants are given 
full decision-making powers such as what to produce and how to 
deal with their products to rally the masses of peasants' 
enthusiasm. Second, the agriculture and rural economy have been 
made market-oriented to give play to market mechanism. 
Actually, these are a successful practice of building a new 
socialist market economic system in rural areas. To continue to 
deepen rural reform, currently we need to do a good job in the 
following three areas: First, while making the household 
contract responsibility system with remuneration linked to 
output more firmly established and making efforts to refine the 
system, we should strive to budget rural economic resources in 
the optimum manner and to enable production elements to flow 
more freely. Second, we should develop rural markets, invigorate 
rural circulation, and take various measures to link the 
decentralized productions of individual households to a unified 
market. Third, the government should provide better guidance 
for agricultural production, give greater support and protection 
to it, strengthen regulation and control over it, and develop a 
better socialized service system. Wen Jiabao continued: Next 
year is a crucial year for our reform; various major reform 
measures will be instituted next year. We must place importance 
on rural work, strengthen agriculture's position as the 
foundation of the national economy, ensure a steady growth in 
grain and cotton production, ensure the supply of agricultural 
and sideline products, and ensure a stable market of these 
products to create a favorable economic climate and a stable 
social environment for the reform. 
  Commenting on the fact that Huaiyin City had reaped bumper 
grain harvests in the past few years but its peasants' income 
had been comparatively low, Wen Jiabao pointed out: Major grain 
and cotton production areas are extremely important to the 
country's grain and cotton production; therefore, we should take 
effective measures to speed up these areas' economic 
development. First, we should regulate the current grain and 
cotton prices by implementing reasonable price policies, so to 
reasonably raise the relatively low prices and to improve the 
relative economic efficiency of grain and cotton production. 
Second, while ensuring a steady increase in grain and cotton 
production, we should make the rural industrial structures more 
rational; should forcefully develop a diversified economy and 
town and village enterprises in rural areas -- in particular, we 
should develop the livestock and poultry industry and the 
processing of agricultural and sideline products; and should 
choose the development path of combining efforts to increase 
production and to develop value-added processing industries. 
Third, governments at all levels should appropriately pool 
their financial resources to support economic development of 
major grain and cotton production areas. 
  Wen Jiabao stressed: The key to deepening rural reform and 
to 
accelerating the economic development in major grain and cotton 
production areas is to have good leaders. Party members and 
grass-roots cadres in rural areas not only should take the lead 
in getting better of, but also should lead the masses to achieve 
common prosperity. He urged grass-roots cadres in rural areas 
to earnestly study Comrade Deng Xiaoping's theory of building 
socialism with Chinese characteristics, to carry through the 
guidelines of the Third Plenary Session of the 14th CPC Central 
Committee and the Central Rural Work Meeting, to emancipate 
their minds, seek truth from facts, be self-reliant, work hard 
to pioneer new spheres of endeavors, and further advance rural 
reform and economic development. 
  Those accompanying Wen Jiabao during his inspection tour 
included Cao Hongmin, deputy secretary of the Jiangsu Provincial 
CPC Committee; and Wan Baorui, vice minister of agriculture. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

