<F P=100> Northeast Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Heilongjiang Burns 500 Kg of `Fake' Tiger Bones </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1201080394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0715 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1201080394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 12 (XINHUA) -- Authorities in 
Harbin have burned some 500 kg of fake tiger bones, Deputy 
Forestry Minister Shen Maocheng said here today. 
  He said the fakes had been confiscated by 30 local 
law-enforcement officers during a week-long crackdown on the 
illegal trade in tiger bones and rhinoceros horns last September. 
  China has strictly banned transaction, transport and use of 
rhinoceros horns and tiger bones, which were used in making 
traditional Chinese medicine. 

</TEXT>

