<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujian Reports Antismuggling Statistics </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1101133394 Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1101133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Fuzhou Fujian People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A provincial feedback meeting about curbing 
smuggling ended in Fuzhou yesterday. It was learned from this 
meeting that since last year, the province handled 2,669 
smuggling cases involving cars, motorcycles, color television 
sets, video recorders, air conditioners, cigarettes, gold, and 
49,406 grams of drugs, the total value being 187 million yuan. 
  At the meeting, Vice Governor Tong Wanheng pointed out: In 
this new year, there is a need to continue to implement the 
spirit of the central meeting on curbing smuggling activities, 
to profoundly carry out a combined operation, and to increase 
the momentum of crackdown to ensure phased achievements in the 
period up to the Spring Festival. 

</TEXT>

